# Lesson 10 -- Foundry SDK chat client (KEYLESS AUTH)
#
# SETUP:
#   1. Run Deploy-Lesson10-Infrastructure.ps1 to provision the Foundry project.
#   2. Copy this file to .env in the demo/ folder.
#   3. Paste the FOUNDRY_PROJECT_ENDPOINT from the deploy script output.
#   4. NEVER commit .env to source control.
#
# L10 is the keyless-auth lesson. NO API KEY in this file. Auth flows through
# DefaultAzureCredential (az login on a laptop; managed identity on Azure compute).
# Your signed-in identity needs the "Cognitive Services OpenAI User" role on the
# Foundry resource -- the deploy script assigns this to you automatically.
#
# FOUNDRY_PROJECT_ENDPOINT is the URL on the Foundry project Overview page:
#   https://ai.azure.com -> your project -> Overview -> Project endpoint
# The format is:
#   https://YOUR-RESOURCE-NAME.services.ai.azure.com/api/projects/YOUR-PROJECT-NAME

FOUNDRY_PROJECT_ENDPOINT=https://YOUR-RESOURCE-NAME.services.ai.azure.com/api/projects/YOUR-PROJECT-NAME
FOUNDRY_MODEL_NAME=gpt-4o
